------------------------- Third assignment ------------------------

8. As a math student,
    I wish to compare lengths in feet and inches.
    1ft = 12in

8. As a math student,
    I wish to compare lengths in inches and cm.
    2in = 5cm

9. As a math student,
    I wish to compare lengths in cm and mm.
    1cm = 10mm

10. As a math student,
    I wish to compare volumes in liter and gallon.
    1 gallon = 3.78 liters

11. As a math student,
    I want to able to add two lengths in inches.
    2in + 2 in = 4in

12. As a math student,
    I want to able to add two lengths in any unit and the standard outputs in inches

13. As a math student(not a good one),
    I want to able to volumes and lengths

    1 gallon = 1 inch

14. As a math student,
    I want to able to add two volumes in any unit and the standard outputs in liters.

    1 gallon + 1 liters = 4.78 ltrs

15. As a math student,
    I want to be able to compare temperature in Fahrenheit and Celsius.

        212f = 100c

----------------------------- Fourth Assignment------------------------------

15. The kingdom of Balloria is known for its wizards and thier colorful magical balls.
    These balls are very powerful and have to be stores safely when not in use.

    As a provider of a service that lets wizards store their balls,
    I'd like a bag that can hold a maximum of 12 balls.

16. As a provider of a service that lets wizards store their balls,
    I'd like a bag that allows a wizard to only put in a maximum of 3 green balls.

17. As a provider of a service that lets wizards store their balls,
    I'd like a bag that prevents a wizard from adding double the number of red balls than green balls.

18. Ballorian law is very strict about the placement of balls.
    If any of the balls violate any of the palcement rules while bring placed next to each other,
    the balls will explode and destroy Balloria.

    As a provider of a service that lets wizards store their balls,
    I have to report any attempt that violates any of the placement rules.

19. As a provider of a service that lets wizards store their balls,
    I'd like a bag that lets a wizard add as many blue balls as a bag can hold.

